text.section:
The Department shall issue a preliminary certificate of registration to a provider if the Department determines that:
the proposed continuing care at home agreement is satisfactory;
the provider has submitted all proposed advertisements, advertising campaigns, and other promotional materials for the program;
the form and substance of all advertisements, advertising campaigns, and other promotional materials submitted are not deceptive, misleading, or likely to mislead;
the information and documents submitted with the feasibility study under § 10-455 of this subtitle are current and accurate or have been updated to make them accurate; and
the provider has submitted any other information that the Department requests.
